h323Gw.name: h323Gw
h323Gw.description: The MIB Module supports the functions of a H323 gateway.

H323gwConnectionCommand.name: H323gwConnectionCommand
H323gwConnectionCommand.description: Commands for a connection: 1. Disconnect 2. Hold (mute) 3. Resume (stop mute) 4. Reset Statistics 5. ...

h323GwSystemTable.name: h323GwSystemTable
h323GwSystemTable.description: This table describes the system information for instances of a gateway.

h323GwSystemEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the system.

h323GwSystemNameAndMaker.name: h323GwSystemNameAndMaker
h323GwSystemNameAndMaker.description: This entity's name and maker name. A textual description of this entity may be appended after the maker name.

h323GwSystemContact.name: h323GwSystemContact
h323GwSystemContact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person.

h323GwSystemLocation.name: h323GwSystemLocation
h323GwSystemLocation.description: The physical location of this system. For instance, closet, terminal room and so on

h323GwSystemUptime.name: h323GwSystemUptime
h323GwSystemUptime.description: The amount of time (in hundredths of a second) since this system was last initialized. Note that this is different from sysUpTime in MIB-II because sysUpTime is the uptime of the network management portion of the system.

h323GwSystemLocalTime.name: h323GwSystemLocalTime
h323GwSystemLocalTime.description: The local date and time of day.

h323GwConfigurationTable.name: h323GwConfigurationTable
h323GwConfigurationTable.description: This table contains configuration information for instances of a gateway.

h323GwConfigurationEntry.description: It contains objects that describe the configuration.

h323GwConfigurationEnableNotifications.name: h323GwConfigurationEnableNotifications
h323GwConfigurationEnableNotifications.description: Indicates whether notifications should be generated for this entity. The default is disabled.

h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddressTa.name: h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddressTag
h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddressTa.description: The alias address tag for the leading alias address.

h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddress.name: h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddress
h323GwConfigurationLeadingAliasAddress.description: The leading alias address, for example, a PBX extension or PTT number, that this gateway is connected to. This leading alias address acts as a prefix, and is of a fixed length.

h323GwConfigurationH323Table.description: This table contains configuration information, specific to H.323, for instances of a gateway.

h323GwConfigurationH323Entry.description: It contains objects that describe the configuration.

h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddress.name: h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddressTag
h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddress.description: Gatekeeper address tag. Specifies how h323GwGatekeeperAddress represents an address. If the gateway does not register with a gatekeeper, it is empty

h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddress.name: h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddress
h323GwConfigurationH323GatekeeperAddress.description: Gatekeeper address. This is the address of the gatekeeper that the gateway was registered with, if at all. If the gateway does not register with a gatekeeper, it is empty

h323GwConfigurationH320Entry.description: It contains objects that describe the configuration.

h323GwConfigurationH320TotalPorts.description: Total number of H320 Ports available to the gateway

h323GwConfigurationPstnTotalPorts.description: Total number of Pstn Ports available to the gateway

h323GwConnectionsTable.name: h323GwConnectionsTable
h323GwConnectionsTable.description: This table contains information about H.323, H.320 and Pstn devices that are connected to a gateway. It is a list of device entries. The number of entries equals to the number of connected devices.

h323GwConnectionsEntry.name: h323GwConnectionsEntry
h323GwConnectionsEntry.description: It contains objects that describe a H.323 device.

h323GwConnectionsEstablishedCallId.name: h323GwConnectionsEstablishedCallId
h323GwConnectionsEstablishedCallId.description: The H.323 call id of the final connection made by a gateway to complete the call between two H.323 devices. For an H.320 or PSTN endpoint, the value of this ID is zero until this endpoint is joined in a call with an H.323 endpoint. The value of this object can be used to index into the h323GwCallsTable.

h323GwConnectionsIndex.name: h323GwConnectionsIndex
h323GwConnectionsIndex.description: An arbitrary index to this table

h323GwConnectionsCommand.name: h323GwConnectionsCommand
h323GwConnectionsCommand.description: A command variable for this connection.

h323GwConnectionsStartTime.name: h323GwConnectionsStartTime
h323GwConnectionsStartTime.description: The start time of this connection. The start time occurs at the first indication of a call request.

h323GwConnectionsTotalErrors.name: h323GwConnectionsTotalErrors
h323GwConnectionsTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors that occurred since this connection was made. The kind of errors that need to be counted are those that are listed in the given probable causes for errors on a connection, in MmErrorProbableCause.

h323GwConnectionsLastError.name: h323GwConnectionsLastError
h323GwConnectionsLastError.description: Probable Cause for the most recent error that has occurred on this connection. This value must be one of the given probable causes for errors on a connection. Values for probable causes for errors on a call or errors on an entity do not apply.

h323GwConnectionsConnectionDirection.name: h323GwConnectionsConnectionDirection
h323GwConnectionsConnectionDirection.description: A direction of the connection from a gateway point of view. In - remote device called the gateway; Out - the gateway called the remote device.

h323GwConnectionsAliasAddressTag.name: h323GwConnectionsAliasAddressTag

h323GwConnectionsAliasAddress.description: The aliasAddress for this connected end point.

h323GwConnectionsH320H221StatsTableIndex.description: The index to the table in H.320 entity mib

h323GwCallsTable.name: h323GwCallsTable
h323GwCallsTable.description: This table contains information about calls between two entities made through a gateway. It is a list of calls. The number of entries equals to the number of calls.

h323GwCallsTableEntry.description: It contains objects that describe a call.

h323GwCallsEstablishedCallId.description: The H.323 call id of the connection made by a gateway to complete the call between two devices.

h323GwCallsNumberOfConnectedDevices.description: The number of devices that are part of this call.

h323GwCallsGatewayAllocatedCallId.description: The call id that is allocated by the gateway. This number is implementation specific.

h323GwCallsStartTime.description: The start time of this call.

h323GwCallsTotalErrors.name: h323GwCallsTotalErrors
h323GwCallsTotalErrors.description: The total number of errors that occurred since the start of this call. The kind of errors that need to be counted are those that are listed in the given probable causes for errors on a call, in MmErrorProbableCause.

h323GwCallsLastError.description: Probable Cause for the most recent error that has occurred on this call. This value must be one of the given probable causes for errors on a call. Values for probable causes for errors on a connection or errors on an entity do not apply.
